Actually, from what you have pasted there it is clearly coming from the UI IDE plugin.  Note those two entries were written at the same time.  The MarkerView class has several lines of code like this:

} catch (CoreException e) {
	IDEWorkbenchPlugin.getDefault().getLog().log(e.getStatus());
}

This will produce exactly the log entries you have shown here because it discards the CoreException and only keeps the status.  This should be changed to:

} catch (CoreException e) {
	IDEWorkbenchPlugin.log(null, e);
}

(an English message could be used in place of "null" above to describe where the error occurred, but it will be evident from the stack trace anyway).
